questions.body:
Given the following Terraform configuration, what will happen when `terraform init` is run?

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    azurerm = {
      source  = "hashicorp/azurerm"
      version = "~> 3.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}
```

What is the difference between a `resource` block and a `data` block in Terraform? Consider the following example:

```hcl
data "azurerm_resource_group" "existing" {
  name = "my-existing-rg"
}

resource "azurerm_linux_virtual_machine" "web" {
  name                = "web-vm"
  resource_group_name = data.azurerm_resource_group.existing.name
  location            = data.azurerm_resource_group.existing.location
}
```

What will the `count` meta-argument do in the following resource block?

```hcl
resource "azurerm_linux_virtual_machine" "web" {
  count               = 3
  name                = "web-${count.index}"
  resource_group_name = azurerm_resource_group.main.name
  location            = azurerm_resource_group.main.location
  size                = "Standard_B1s"
  tags = {
    Name = "web-${count.index}"
  }
}
```

What does the following Terraform expression produce?

```hcl
locals {
  tags = {
    Environment = var.environment
    Project     = var.project_name
  }
  merged_tags = merge(local.tags, { ManagedBy = "terraform" })
}
```
